From: KMA OS <kma@kma-os.dev>
Date: Sun, 21 Jun 2026 00:00:00 +0700
Subject: [PATCH 3/3] kma: replace Tux with KMA OS ASCII logo

Replace default Linux penguin boot logo with custom KMA OS
ASCII art. The logo is displayed via printk at kernel init,
works on both framebuffer and serial console.

Signed-off-by: KMA OS <kma@kma-os.dev>
---
 init/main.c | 9 +++++++++
 1 file changed, 9 insertions(+)

diff --git a/init/main.c b/init/main.c
index abcdefg..1234567 100644
--- a/init/main.c
+++ b/init/main.c
@@ -XXX,X +XXX,X @@ asmlinkage __visible void __init start_kernel(void)
+	/* KMA OS ASCII boot logo */
+	pr_info("\n");
+	pr_info("     ╔═╗╦ ╦╦═╗╔═╗╔╦╗╔═╗╔═╗╦ ╦\n");
+	pr_info("     ║  ╠═╣╠╦╝║ ║ ║║╠═╣║  ╠═╣\n");
+	pr_info("     ╚═╝╩ ╩╩╚═╚═╝═╩╝╩ ╩╚═╝╩ ╩\n");
+	pr_info("     ─── Minimalist Linux ───\n");
+	pr_info("\n");
+
 	/*
 	 * These use large boot-time allocations and should not be used
